{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:7.85pt 0cm 0.0001pt;line-height:normal;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;\">The purpose of this\ncourse is to guide students in gaining practical understanding of intercultural\ncommunication as a necessary, targeted response to the opportunities and\ndifficulties that are currently emerging in the global corporate environment.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;margin-top:7.85pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;\">This course offers an\nintroduction to core ideas of intercultural communication and their\napplications to a wide range of circumstances.</span></p>", "到達目標": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt;line-height:normal;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;\">Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt;line-height:normal;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;\">Demonstrate a critical appreciation of diverse social, cultural, and\nsub-cultural identities relevant to contexts for intercultural communication;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt;line-height:normal;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;\">Discover the complexity of communication in an intercultural\ncommunication exchange;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;\">Making and justifying decisions that impact on the work and learning of\npeople from diverse social and cultural backgrounds;</span><span times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\";\"=\"roman';'\" style=\"font-family:Symbol;text-indent:-18pt;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:7pt;line-height:normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt;line-height:normal;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;background-image:initial;background-position:initial;background-size:initial;background-repeat:initial;background-attachment:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;\">Instruction methods used in this course will\ninclude interactive seminars, self-assessment, group discussions, and case\ndiscussions in small groups and an entire class.&nbsp; Learning in this course\nrequires participants’ proactive participation and dedicated involvement in\nboth class and group discussions.&nbsp; Small group discussion, especially, is\na key function in which to increase participants to learn throughout this\ncourse.&nbsp; Thus, participants will be encouraged to share their views and\nideas with other members actively.</span></p>", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span arial\",